data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","sequence_number":185,"item_id":"msg_0042bc977cf58627006933635756b881948b2dff604d4e26df","output_index":2,"content_index":0,"text":"Contoso Electronics has a Whistleblower Policy designed to maintain a safe and transparent working environment. This policy encourages employees to report any unethical or illegal activities they witness. \n\n**Key elements of the policy include:**\n\n- **Scope:** Applies to all employees, contractors, and third parties.\n- **Definition:** A whistleblower is someone who reports illegal, unethical, or non-compliant activities.\n- **Reporting Procedures:** Reports can be made by contacting Human Resources, emailing the Compliance Officer at compliance@contoso.com, or calling the Compliance Hotline at 1-800-555-1212. Anonymous reporting is an option.\n- **Non-retaliation:** Retaliation against whistleblowers is strictly prohibited.\n- **Confidentiality:** Whistleblower identities are kept confidential to the extent permitted by law.\n- **Investigation:** All reports will be investigated promptly.","logprobs":[]}

